The President gave remarks at an iftar dinner celebrating the Islamic holy month of Ramadan. He thanked various officials and members of the Muslim community for being present. He highlighted the importance of the iftar dinner in bringing families and friends together to promote peace, clarity, and love. The President also expressed gratitude for the partnerships and friendships formed with Muslim-majority countries and emphasized the need for collaboration in achieving security and prosperity for all. He concluded by calling for prayers for peace and justice and a bright future.